---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { buildCanonicalUrl } from '../../lib/podcast';

const canonicalUrl = buildCanonicalUrl(Astro.site, '/');
const pageTitle = '5 Best Dinosaur Podcasts You Should Be Listening To';
const pageDescription = 'Find out the top 5 podcasts about dinosaurs and paleontology';
---

<BaseLayout
  title={pageTitle}
  description={pageDescription}
  canonicalUrl={canonicalUrl}
  ogType="article"
>
  <p class="back-link">
    <a href="/">← All episodes</a>
  </p>
  
  <article class="episode-article">
    <header class="episode-article__header">
      <h1>{pageTitle}</h1>
      <p>Podcasts are one of the best ways to explore the prehistoric world. Whether you're looking for scientific deep dives, expert interviews, or immersive storytelling, these are the <strong>top dinosaur podcasts you should be listening to right now</strong>.
  </p>
    <a href="https://iknowdino.com/" target="_blank">
        <h2>1. I Know Dino: The Big Dinosaur Podcast</h2>
        <img src="/img/i-know-dino.jpeg" class="podcast-thumb" alt="I Know Dino Podcast Logo" />
    </a>
    <p>
        One of the most established dinosaur podcasts, <em>I Know Dino</em> delivers consistent, high-quality episodes covering
        the latest paleontology news, dinosaur facts, and expert interviews. With a long track record and a loyal audience,
        it’s a go-to resource for anyone who wants to stay up to date with discoveries in the field.
    </p>
    <p><strong>Best for:</strong> News, weekly updates, and comprehensive dinosaur coverage</p>

    <a href="https://terriblelizards.libsyn.com/" target="_blank">
        <h2>2. Terrible Lizards</h2>
        <img src="/img/terrible-lizards.jpeg" class="podcast-thumb" alt="Terrible Lizards Podcast Logo"/>
    </a>
    <p>
        Hosted by a paleontologist and a comedian, <em>Terrible Lizards</em> strikes a great balance between scientific accuracy
        and entertainment. The conversational format makes complex topics easy to understand, while still diving deep into
        fascinating questions about dinosaur biology and behavior.
    </p>
    <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Engaging discussions with a mix of science and humor</p>

    <a href="/" target="_blank">
        <h2>3. Dinosaur Stories Podcast</h2>
        <img src="/logo.jpg" class="podcast-thumb" alt="Dinosaur Stories Podcast Logo"/>
    </a>
    <p>
        If you’re looking for a more immersive experience, <em>Dinosaur Stories Podcast</em> offers a fresh take on prehistoric
        life through storytelling. Each episode focuses on a specific dinosaur—like <em>Tyrannosaurus rex</em>—and blends modern
        scientific understanding with vivid, narrative-driven conversations.
    </p>
    <p>
        Instead of just listing facts, the show brings dinosaurs to life, helping listeners imagine how these incredible
        creatures lived, hunted, and survived. It’s an excellent choice for both newcomers and enthusiasts who want something
        more cinematic and engaging.
    </p>
    <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Story-driven, entertaining, and educational dinosaur episodes</p>

    <a href="https://www.paleonerds.com/" target="_blank">
        <h2>4. Paleo Nerds</h2>
        <img src="/img/paleo-nerds.jpeg" class="podcast-thumb" alt="Paleo Nerds Podcast Logo"/>
    </a>
    <p>
        <em>Paleo Nerds</em> focuses on interviews with scientists, authors, and creators in the world of paleontology. It offers
        valuable insights into the people behind the discoveries, making it a great podcast for listeners who want a deeper
        understanding of the science and research process.
    </p>
    <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Interviews and behind-the-scenes paleontology</p>

    <a href="https://chasmosaurs.com/">
        <h2>5. Love in the Time of Chasmosaurs</h2>
        <img src="/img/chasmosaurs.jpg" class="podcast-thumb" alt="Love in the Time of Chasmosaurs Podcast Logo"/>
    </a>
    <p>
        This podcast explores the intersection of dinosaurs, science, and culture. From paleoart to books and media,
        <em>Love in the Time of Chasmosaurs</em> offers a unique perspective that goes beyond fossils and into how we imagine
        and represent prehistoric life.
    </p>
    <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Dinosaur culture, paleoart, and creative discussions</p>

    <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem">Final Thoughts</h2>
    <p>
        The world of dinosaur podcasts is growing, but each show brings something different to the table. Whether you prefer
        scientific updates, expert interviews, or immersive storytelling, there’s never been a better time to explore the age
        of dinosaurs.
    </p>
    <p>
        If you're just getting started, <em>Dinosaur Stories Podcast</em> is a great entry point—combining accurate science with
        compelling storytelling that makes prehistoric life feel more real than ever.
    </p>

    </header>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
